2:
He sprouts from the ground like a flower and is cut down;
\q he flees like a shadow and does not last.
\q

10:
But man dies; he becomes weak;
\q indeed, man stops breathing, and then where is he?
\q

16:
You would number and care for my footsteps;
\q you would not keep track of my sin.
\q

17:
My transgression would be sealed up in a bag;
\q you would cover up my iniquity.
\m

18:
But even mountains fall and come to nothing;
\q even rocks are moved out of their place;
\q

19:
the waters wear down the stones;
\q their flooding washes away the dust of the earth.
\q Like this, you destroy the hopes of man.

20:
You always defeat him, and he passes away;
\q you change his face and send him away to die.
\q

21:
If his sons are honored, he does not know it;
\q and if they are brought low, he does not see it.
\q
